review_comments.body:
There is no automated regression test covering the `CURLSHOPT_UNSHARE` invalid-type path that previously triggered UB (e.g., `type >= 32`). Adding a small libtest that calls `curl_share_setopt(share, CURLSHOPT_UNSHARE, 32)` and asserts it returns `CURLSHE_BAD_OPTION` would help prevent future regressions.
```suggestion
    if(!res) {
      if((type >= 0) && (type < (int)(sizeof(share->specifier) * 8)))
        share->specifier &= ~(unsigned int)(1 << type);
      else
        res = CURLSHE_BAD_OPTION;
    }
```

